This dashboard provides an interactive analysis of Amazon bestselling books from 2009–2019
focusing on patterns in ratings, reviews, price,genre, and publication year. The visualizations
highlight how reader engagement varies across different types of books and reveal trends in book
popularity over time. By exploring the relationships between price, reviews, and ratings the
dashboard helps identify factors associated with highly successful titles. Interactive elements
allow users to filter and explore the data more closely, providing a cleaer view of how different
variables influence reader behavior and market trends.
